Manila Water Co. (MWC)  shares rose the
most in a month on the Philippine Stock Exchange following an
agreement by the utilityâ€™s  South Asia  unit to purchase a 31.5
percent stake in Saigon Water Infrastructure Corp.  Manila Water, which serves half of the Philippine capital,
closed 2.1 percent higher at 31.60 pesos, the second-biggest
gainer today on the 19-member Bloomberg World Water Index. The
stock has slipped 1.3 percent this year compared with a 1.7
